---
description: Technical implementation rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Use a simple stack optimized for speed.

Preferred stack:

- Next.js / React
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Local mock data first
- Open-Meteo API for real forecast data
- Supabase only if persistence is needed

Code rules:

- Keep components small.
- Prefer readable code over clever abstractions.
- Mock hard parts when needed for demo.
- Use clear names: BeachCard, SurfScore, ReportCondition, PersonalAnalytics.
- Do not build unnecessary architecture.
- All demo flows must work without real login.

Default pages:

- /login
- /dashboard
- /beach/[id]
- /reports
- /analytics
